    <div class="w3-twothird w3-container">
      <p> br <br> </p>
      <h1 class="w3-text-brown">Language and Dialects</h1> 
      <p>The Kadazan-Dusun people speak a language from the Austronesian family, commonly called the Kadazan-Dusun language. It comprises several dialects that reflect the geographic diversity of the community. These dialects, such as Bundu, Rungus, and Liwan, are mutually intelligible but carry unique linguistic nuances and vocabularies. The richness of the language showcases the community's adaptability across Sabah’s varied landscapes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="w3-third w3-container"> <div id="2.1">
      <p> BR <br> </p>
